Package com.Game.model.order

Class BlockadeOrder

java.lang.Object
com.Game.model.order.Order
com.Game.model.order.BlockadeOrder
public class BlockadeOrder extends Order
Represents a blockade order in the game. When executed, the specified territory is turned into a neutral territory, its owner is removed, and the number of armies is tripled. In the Command pattern, this is a concrete Command implementation.

  • Method Details

    • execute

      public void execute()
      Executes the blockade order. The method removes the territory from its current owner, sets the territory's owner to null, triples the number of armies in the territory, and prints the details of the operation. In the Command pattern, this is the concrete implementation of the execute() method.
      Specified by:
      execute in class Order
